\pard\page\up6\f0\fs16 #K\up0\f1\fs20  \up6\f0\fs16 $\up0\f1\fs20  \b Close command (File menu)\b0\par
\par
Use this command to close all windows containing the active document.  AndyCAD suggests that you save changes to your document before you close it.  If you close a document without saving, you lose all changes made since the last time you saved it.  Before closing an untitled document, AndyCAD displays the \uldb Save As dialog box\ulnone\v\f0 AFX_HIDD_FILESAVE\v0\f1  and suggests that you name and save the document.\par
\par
You can also close a document by using the Close icon on the document's window, as shown below:\par
\{bml scmenu.bmp\}\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #K\up0\f1\fs20  \up6\f0\fs16 $\up0\f1\fs20  \b Save command (File menu)\b0\par
\par
Use this command to save the active document to its current name and directory.  When you save a document for the first time, AndyCAD displays the \uldb Save As dialog box\ulnone\v\f0 AFX_HIDD_FILESAVE\v0\f1  so you can name your document.  If you want to change the name and directory of an existing document before you save it, choose the \uldb Save As command\ulnone\v\f0 HID_FILE_SAVE_AS\v0\f1 .\par
\par
\b Shortcuts\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Toolbar:\tab\{bmc filesave.bmp\}\par
Keys:\tab CTRL+S\par
\pard\li360\par
\pard\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #K\up0\f1\fs20  \up6\f0\fs16 $\up0\f1\fs20  \b Save As command (File menu)\b0\par
\par
Use this command to save and name the active document.  AndyCAD displays the \uldb Save As dialog box\ulnone\v\f0 AFX_HIDD_FILESAVE\v0\f1  so you can name your document.  \par
\par
To save a document with its existing name and directory, use the \uldb Save command\ulnone\v\f0 HID_FILE_SAVE\v0\f1 .\par
\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Send command (File menu)\b0\par
\par
Use this command to send the active document through electronic mail.  This command presents a mail window with the active document attached to it.  You may then fill out the To: field, Subject: field, etc., and add text to the body of the message if you wish.  When you are finished you may click the "Send" button to send the message.\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 File Save As dialog box\par
\b0\par
The following options allow you to specify the name and location of the file you're about to save:\par
\pard\sb60\b File Name\par
\pard\li360\b0 Type a new filename to save a document with a different name.  AndyCAD adds the extension you specify in the Save File As Type box.\par
\pard\sb60\b Drives\par
\pard\li360\b0 Select the drive in which you want to store the document.\par
\pard\sb60\b Directories\par
\pard\li360\b0 Select the directory in which you want to store the document.\par
\pard\sb60\b Network...\par
\pard\li360\b0 Choose this button to connect to a network location, assigning it a new drive letter. \par
\par
