\pard\page\up6\f0\fs16 #K\up0\f1\fs20  \up6\f0\fs16 $\b\up0\f1\fs20 Status Bar command (View menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to display and hide the Status Bar, which describes the action to be executed by the selected menu item or depressed toolbar button, and keyboard latch state. A check mark appears next to the menu item when the Status Bar is displayed.\par
\par
See \uldb Status Bar\ulnone\v AFX_HIDW_STATUS_BAR\v0  for help on using the status bar.\par
