\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Size command (System menu)\b0\f0\par
\par
\f1 Use this command to display a four-headed arrow so you can size the active window with the arrow keys.\par
\{bml curarw4.bmp\}\par
\par
After the pointer changes to the four-headed arrow:\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sb60 1.\tab Press one of the DIRECTION keys (left, right, up, or down arrow key) to move the pointer to the border you want to move.  \par
2.\tab Press a DIRECTION key to move the border.\par
3.\tab Press ENTER when the window is the size you want.\par
\pard\par
Note:  This command is unavailable if you maximize the window.\par
\f0\par
\b\f1 Shortcut\f0\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0\f1 Mouse:\tab Drag the size bars at the corners or edges of the window.\par
\pard\li360\par
\pard\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Move command (Control menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to display a four-headed arrow so you can move the active window or dialog box with the arrow keys.\par
\{bmc curarw4.bmp\}\par
\par
Note:  This command is unavailable if you maximize the window.\par
\par
\b Shortcut\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Keys:\tab CTRL+F7\par
\par
\pard\tx1440\page\up6\f0\fs16 #$\b\up0\f1\fs20 Minimize command (application Control menu)\par
\pard\b0\par
Use this command to reduce the AndyCAD window to an icon.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\b\f0\par
\f1 Shortcut\b0\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440 Mouse:\tab Click the minimize icon \{bmc scmin.bmp\} on the title bar.\par
Keys:\tab ALT+F9\par
\pard\fi-360\li1080\f0\par
\pard\f1\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Maximize command (System menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to enlarge the active window to fill the available space.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\b\par
Shortcut\b0\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440 Mouse:\tab Click the maximize icon \{bmc scmax.bmp\} on the title bar; or double-click the title bar.\par
Keys:\tab CTRL+F10 enlarges a document window.\par
\pard\fi-360\li1080\f0\par
\pard\f1\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Next Window command (document Control menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to switch to the next open document window.  AndyCAD determines which window is next according to the order in which you opened the windows.\par
\par
\b Shortcut\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Keys:\tab CTRL+F6\par
\pard\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Previous Window command (document Control menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to switch to the previous open document window.  AndyCAD determines which window is previous according to the order in which you opened the windows.\par
\par
\b Shortcut\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Keys:\tab SHIFT+CTRL+F6\par
\pard\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Close command (Control menus)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to close the active window or dialog box.\par
\par
Double-clicking a Control-menu box is the same as choosing the Close command.\par
\{bml appexit.bmp\}\par
\par
Note:  If you have multiple windows open for a single document, the Close command on the document Control menu closes only one window at a time.  You can close all windows at once with the Close command on the File menu.\par
\par
\b Shortcuts\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Keys: \tab CTRL+F4 closes a document window\par
\tab ALT+F4 closes the <<YourType>> window or dialog box\par
\pard\tab\tab\tab\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Restore command (Control menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to return the active window to its size and position before you chose the Maximize or Minimize command.\par
\page\up6\f0\fs16 #\b\up0\f1\fs20 Switch to command (application Control menu)\par
\b0\par
Use this command to display a list of all open applications.  Use this "Task List" to switch to or close an application on the list.\par
\par
\b Shortcut\par
\pard\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\b0 Keys:\tab CTRL+ESC\par
\pard\par
\b Dialog Box Options\par
\b0 When you choose the Switch To command, you will be presented with a dialog box with the following options:\par
\pard\sb60\b Task List\par
\pard\li360\b0 Select the application you want to switch to or close.\par
\pard\sb60\b Switch To\par
\pard\li360\b0 Makes the selected application active.\par
\pard\sb60\b End Task\par
\pard\li360\b0 Closes the selected application.\par
\pard\sb60\b Cancel\par
\pard\li360\b0 Closes the Task List box.\par
\pard\sb60\b Cascade\par
\pard\li360\b0 Arranges open applications so they overlap and you can see each title bar.  This option does not affect applications reduced to icons.\par
\pard\sb60\b Tile\par
\pard\li360\b0 Arranges open applications into windows that do not overlap.  This option does not affect applications reduced to icons.\par
\pard\sb60\b Arrange Icons\par
\pard\li360\b0 Arranges the icons of all minimized applications across the bottom of the screen.\par
